title: The 7th Victim (1943 horror/noir)
description:
<a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0036341/" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0036341/</a>

Produced by the famous B-movie producer/screenwriter, Val Lewton, The 7th Victim is one of the first films ever to depict a Satanic cult. This was a very off-beat and risque theme for the time. There is excellent development of vulnerable and sensitive characters, and a prosaic portrayal of the cult not typical of current depictions.

In contrast to my other uploads, this movie is more in the vein of psychological horror, than noir, but it is the sort of that movie noir fans are likely to enjoy anyway.
